<TITLE> Romanian PM nominates new farm minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BUCHAREST, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Romanian Prime Minister Calin Tariceanu nominated farm ministry official Dacian Ciolos on Friday to replace sacked agriculture minister Decebal Traian Remes, the government said. Remes lost his job on Thursday after he became embroiled in a sleaze scandal just as the European Commission gave Romania an ultimatum to overhaul its agricultural payments system or face cuts in European Union aid. "Dacian Ciolos ... has solid experience in relations with European Union institutions in the field of agriculture," the government said in a statement. Ciolos, 38, a French-educated official who used to work at the European Commission delegation to Bucharest, has to be approved by President Traian Basescu before he takes over the agriculture portfolio. The Commission's ultimatum on farm aid and the media scandal surrounding Remes are the latest blows to Tariceanu's embattled government, which narrowly survived a parliamentary no-confidence vote last week. The EU executive has said that, 10 months after joining the bloc, Romania still needed to prepare land registries and databases needed to receive subsidi
